# Java OOP & Design Patterns Mini Project

This is a beginner-friendly Java mini project created to demonstrate core Object-Oriented Programming concepts and common software design patterns.

## Concepts Covered
- Encapsulation
- Inheritance
- Polymorphism
- Abstraction
- Singleton Pattern
- Factory Pattern
- Builder Pattern
- Basic client-server and REST API understanding

## Project Description
This project simulates a simple user management and notification system. It includes different user roles, notification methods, and object creation patterns.

## Technologies Used
- Java
- VS Code
- GitHub

## How to Run
1. Clone this repository.
2. Open the folder in VS Code.
3. Compile and run `Main.java`.

## What I Learned
Through this project, I strengthened my understanding of OOP principles and how design patterns can make software more structured, reusable, and easier to maintain.